# Inside .xcodeproj: keep project.pbxproj and xcshareddata, drop user state.
*.xcodeproj/xcuserdata/
*.xcodeproj/project.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/
*.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/

# We commit exactly ONE shared scheme — Tailspot.xcscheme — so that
# xcodebuild works on fresh clones without manual setup. Any OTHER
# scheme file is ignored: Xcode's "Edit Scheme..." dialog saves
# environment variables (including credentials like OPENSKY_CLIENT_SECRET)
# into shared schemes by default, and we've had two leaks from this.
#
# IMPORTANT: edits to the tracked Tailspot.xcscheme are visible to git
# (gitignore doesn't apply to already-tracked files). If you edit the
# scheme in Xcode and Xcode rewrites the file with env vars in it,
# THOSE CHANGES WILL BE STAGED. Always inspect the diff before commit.
# Add env vars to a user-only scheme (xcuserdata/, gitignored), not
# the shared one.
**/*.xcodeproj/xcshareddata/xcschemes/*.xcscheme
!**/*.xcodeproj/xcshareddata/xcschemes/Tailspot.xcscheme
**/*.xcworkspace/xcshareddata/xcschemes/

